Class AbstractGraphItemClient<S extends IGraphItemSettings>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pikater.web.vaadin.gui.client.kineticengine.graph.AbstractGraphItemClient<S>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - The class representing visual settings to this graph item.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IKineticShapeWrapper
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BoxGraphItemClient, EdgeGraphItemClient

    public abstract class AbstractGraphItemClient<S extends IGraphItemSettings>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IKineticShapeWrapper
    Abstract class for all graph items used in experiment editor. Currently, that means boxes and edges.

    SkyCrawl

      • setRegisteredInKinetic

        protected abstract void setRegisteredInKinetic(boolean registered)
        If to be registered, the item is guaranteed not to be selected or registered. Otherwise, it is guaranteed to be registered and not to be selected.

        TIPS:
        • Access the environment using the getKineticEngine() method.
        • Use the KineticEngine.getContainer(EngineComponent engineComponent) method to access the right kinetic container.
        • Register the item with the net.edzard.kinetic.Container#add() method.

      • destroyInnerNodes
